according to maslow's theory of needs how many of those are being fulfilled in your life in brief base needs include air food water sex homeostatis etc medium needs security love belonging self esteem etc and top needs being for self actualization i e personal morality acceptance of facts tricky and lack of prejudice do you agree that all are actual human needs and how would not attaining any one of them impact an individual to be honest with you and myself maslow's theory of needs is probably the best judge of satisfaction i've ever seen i've found that for a little while months to years i can pacify myself convince myself that i've got what i need and i can function great then ever so often i feel just how lost i am without the thing s i'm missing most and it invades every part of my life making me focus on it intensely until i can satisfy it and it doesn't go away until i can satisfy it in some way you see many of us try to pass some of our medium needs and go right up to self actualization Maslow's hierarchy of needs Abraham Maslow Ethics Motivation Summa Theologiae Friedrich Schleiermacher Religion Narcissism Social justice Sexual orientation Social psychology Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Goodness and value theory Objectivist philosophy Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Humanistic psychology Art Abortion debate Happiness Nicomachean Ethics Supernatural Psychotherapy Sin Altruism Theory X and theory Y Sant Thakar Singh Alignment (role-playing games) Merit Sex and the City Human Potential Movement Evil God Human Philipp Melanchthon Marginalism Gender role Patriotism The Skeptical Environmentalist Microeconomics IP (complexity) Same-sex marriage Spiritism Contract Economics Animal rights Discourse ethics Storytelling Infantilism Unidentified flying object Project Blue Book Gospel of Thomas Child sexuality Polyamory Simone Weil Utilitarianism Socrates A Course In Miracles Universal pragmatics Intelligent design Reincarnation Current teac